program, complete with new regulations, to achieve extra cuts in greenhouse =
emissions. The Legislature authorized such rules in 1991.=20
Environmentalists will team up this fall with religious and other groups to =
sponsor public meetings where citizens can present ideas for a Texas greenho=
use-gas plan, said Tom "Smitty" Smith, state director of Public Citizen.=20
"There are clearly a number of things the state could do by rules," he said,=
 "and hopefully we want this to become an issue in the next governor's race.=
"=20
The Sierra Club's state director, Ken Kramer, said Bush's stance on the Kyot=
o pact, and the absence of an alternative proposal by his administration so =
far, appears to be backfiring. Despite U.S. opposition, the treaty was endor=
sed by 178 nations last month in Bonn, Germany.=20
"An ironic aspect of President Bush's failure to come to grips with the glob=
al warming issue is that other people, who definitely see this is something =
that can't be ignored, are rising to the occasion and putting in extra effor=
t because they can't rely on the present administration for leadership," Kra=
mer said.=20
