lug. In May this year, the managing director of a power generation company s=
witched off its generating stations to pressurise the government-owned GRIDC=
O into clearing its dues. The Government in desperation sought to bring abou=
t order by threatening to arrest the managing director. The bad blood contin=
ues to linger.=20
Foreign power companies locking horns with state governments is nothing new.=
